node.text: None of us intended the Red Table to become our Day jobs. The power of the table has transformed our relationships with one another as well as with many of our loved ones in our lives. RTT team members and their families are healing and transforming as well.  So … some members of the RTT family put this RTT reel together as a heartfelt thank you to the many guests and RTT supporters for being a part of an always amazing, sometimes extremely difficult journey. Thank you for sharing your testimonies so that we have an opportunity to know that we are not alone, to know that it’s never too late to change and do better and that life is not about NOT falling but that life is about HOW you rise from the many inevitable falls. I’m grateful for the table and the accountability and spiritual healing it has brought to my life. It has changed me. Thank you to all of you who have approached me in the world with your stories, tears full of healing transformation and appreciation. Life is trying BUT … we are in this together … one step at a time … learning and growing … together. Here is to Love and grace. With deep, deep gratitude … thank you❣️❣️❣️❣️❣️✨🙌🏽✨

node.text:
as we discuss how women are drinking A LOT of alcohol. It’s a trend that has been happening for awhile but since the pandemic, it’s been illuminated that women are abusing alcohol more and more to cope. In my 20’s I was a binge drinker and experimented with several types of mind altering substances. In this clip I speak on an incident that happened to me in the make up trailer on Nutty Professor after a weekend of partying. It was a moment that I began to understand that something had to change. Thank you to @judmurd who was my makeup artist at the time and hung in there with the young Jada that was trying to manage and find her way.  I’m getting there😜

Call someone today and thank them for not giving up on you while you were in your mess✨
STREAMING NOW! LINK IN BIO✨
